Key Match Events: England won by 8 wickets (with 101 balls remaining)
England chased the target in 3.1 overs, scoring 50/2
Pre-Game Insights: England aimed to revive their rocky title defence against Oman
England needed to win their remaining games and for Australia to beat Scotland to have a chance of making the next round
Oman had a valiant Super Over defeat to Namibia and a solid start with the ball against Australia before a listless display against Scotland
Oman was the 19th-ranked team in the world and had the most drops in the T20 World Cup
Captain Aqib Ilyas lamented the number of dot balls faced in their previous match against Scotland
Miscellaneous Highlights: This was the first meeting between England and Oman in a full international fixture
Despite playing 13 times at the Sir Vivian Richards Stadium, this was England's first T20I at the venue
Zeeshan Maqsood needed two more wickets to become the second Oman player with 50 T20I wickets after Bilal Khan
